    summary: 'Jewish philosopher who converted to Catholicism, became a Carmelite nun, and died at Auschwitz.',
    biography: 'Edith Stein was a brilliant Jewish philosopher — a student of Edmund Husserl and herself a pioneering phenomenologist — who converted to Catholicism after reading the autobiography of St. Teresa of Ávila in one night. She became a Carmelite nun under the name Teresa Benedicta of the Cross. After the Nazis began targeting Jewish converts, she was arrested with her sister Rosa and transported to Auschwitz, where she was gassed. She saw her death as a participation in the cross of Christ on behalf of her Jewish people.',
    pathToSainthood: 'Beatified in 1987, canonized by Pope John Paul II on October 11, 1998. Named co-patroness of Europe.',
