    summary: 'Italian teenager who used the internet to catalog Eucharistic miracles, died of leukemia at 15.',
    biography: 'Carlo Acutis was an ordinary Italian teenager with an extraordinary love of the Eucharist. A gifted computer programmer from a young age, he created a website cataloging every reported Eucharistic miracle in history. He died of leukemia at 15 in 2006. Pope Francis beatified him in 2020 — he is widely called the "patron saint of the internet" and the first millennial to be beatified. He is on the fast track to full canonization, with his beatification miracle being the healing of a Brazilian child with a rare pancreatic condition.',
    pathToSainthood: 'Beatified by Pope Francis on October 10, 2020. Canonization expected soon.',
