    summary: 'The "Lily of the Mohawks," the first Native American saint.',
    biography: 'Kateri (Catherine) Tekakwitha was the daughter of a Mohawk chief and an Algonquin Christian mother who died in a smallpox epidemic that also killed her father and brother and left Kateri partially blind and disfigured. Baptized Catholic at 20 by a Jesuit missionary, she endured intense persecution from her tribe and fled to a Christian Native settlement near Montreal. There she lived a life of extraordinary piety, penance, and care for the sick and elderly, dying at age 24. At her death, witnesses reported her face became radiant and her smallpox scars disappeared.',
