    summary: 'Mystic who received the stigmata, convinced the Pope to return to Rome from Avignon.',
    biography: 'Caterina di Giacomo di Benincasa was the 24th of 25 children born to a Sienese dyer. From childhood she experienced mystical visions and refused all marriage proposals. She joined the Dominican Third Order and spent years in intense solitary prayer and penance before emerging to nurse plague victims and criminals facing execution. She corresponded with kings, queens, cardinals, and popes — urging the return of the papacy from Avignon to Rome, which ultimately succeeded. Her "Dialogue" is one of the great mystical texts.',
