    biography: 'Jeanne d\'Arc was an illiterate peasant girl from Domrémy in northeastern France who, at age 13, began hearing the voices of St. Michael, St. Catherine of Alexandria, and St. Margaret of Antioch urging her to aid the French Dauphin and drive out the English. At age 17 she presented herself to Charles VII, convinced him of her divine mission, was given command of the French army, and broke the siege of Orléans — a turning point in the Hundred Years War. Captured by Burgundian allies of England, she was tried for heresy and sorcery in a politically motivated trial and burned alive at the stake at age 19.',
